---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Common Autism Meltdown Triggers & How to Identify Them | Neurosage Hub"
  description="Learn the most common sensory, environmental, and emotional triggers for autism meltdowns, and how to use a trigger log to spot patterns and prevent overwhelm."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
    <nav class="text-sm text-stone-400 mb-8">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-stone-600">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">/</span>
      <a href="/autism-meltdowns" class="hover:text-stone-600">Autism Meltdowns</a>
      <span class="mx-2">/</span>
      <span class="text-stone-600">Triggers</span>
    </nav>
    <h1 class="text-display font-bold text-stone-900 mb-6">Common Autism Meltdown Triggers</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-10">
      Most meltdowns don't come out of nowhere. Learning to identify your child's specific triggers is one of the most powerful steps you can take.
    </p>
    <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none">
      <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm italic">Subpage content — full article goes here (Day 6 of build timeline).</p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
